| First Map of an Extrasolar Planet                                  |
|   from the google-not-earth dept.                                  |
|   posted by ScuttleMonkey on Sunday May 13, @08:15 (Space)         |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/13/128206       |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]jiawen writes "Data from the Spitzer Space Telescope has been used by
researchers to make the first-ever [1]map of an extrasolar planet. It's a
weather map, more precisely, showing temperature variations over the
surface of a [2]Hot Jupiter. It really is hot: even the coldest regions
are about [3]1200 degrees F."

