| AMD Promises Open Source Graphics Drivers                          |
|   from the feel-the-love-linux-gamers dept.                        |
|   posted by Zonk on Sunday May 13, @14:42 (Graphics)               |
|   http://linux.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/13/1659245        |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]MoxFulder writes "Henri Richard, AMD's VP of sales, has [1]promised to
deliver open-source drivers for ATI graphics cards (recently acquired by
AMD) at the recent [2]Red Hat Summit. A series of good news for
proponents of open-source device drivers. In the last year, Intel, the
leading provider of integrated graphics cards, has opened their drivers
as well. But ATI and NVidia, the only two players in the market for
high-performance discrete graphics cards, have so far released only
closed-source drivers for their cards. This has created numerous
compatibility, stability, and ethical problems for users of Linux and
other open source OSes, and prompted projects like [3]Nouveau to try and
reverse-engineer NVidia drivers. Hopefully AMD's decision will put
pressure on NVidia to release open-source drivers as well!"

Discuss this story at:
    http://linux.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/05/13/1659245

Links:
    0. http://toleressea.net/
    1. http://enterpriselinuxlog.blogs.techtarget.com/2007/05/09/amd-will-deliver-open-graphics-drivers/
    2. http://www.redhat.com/summit
    3. http://nouveau.freedesktop.org/


